data.text:
Doubleday, Page & Company, New York (1909), (1909). Doubleday, Page & Company, New York (1909). Green cloth over boards, with black drawing of sailing ship on ocean, small sailing ship at spine, gold lettering. Six sfull page, black and white illustrations by famous illustrators of the time, all named .

A collection of short stories by the author of the Jungle book, Kim and Just So Stories. Each story is followed by a poem, so if you like If, this may also be a book for you. Very Good / No DJ. Item #1031

Doubleday, Page & Company, New York, First Edition, First Printing 1909. Stated: Copyright, 1909 by Rudyard Kipling, Published October, 1909. Very Good. solid, very little pulling of spine at top, clean, text bright and no foxing. slight marking on front end paper from a possible label. slight bumping of corners. Green cloth over boards, with black drawing of sailing ship on ocean, small sailing ship at spine, gold lettering.

Six full page, black and white illustrations by famous illustrators of the time, all named.
